{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17642470","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17642470"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:41:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:41:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17947"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17947","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17947"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.09,0.05,0.23,0.5,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10661"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72993"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10661","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10661"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17947"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58464"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24834"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24835"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72993","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72993"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe bregma is a significant anatomical landmark on the human skull, often used in medical and anthropological contexts.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following describes the sutures that meet at the bregma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Coronal and temporal","Temporal and sagittal","Sagittal and lamboidal","Coronal and sagittal","Temporal and lamboidal"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe bregma is the point on the skull where the \u003Cstrong\u003Ecoronal and sagittal\u003C/strong\u003E sutures intersect. This landmark is located at the top of the skull and is important for various measurements and surgical procedures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options involve other sutures that do not meet at the bregma:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECoronal and temporal\u003C/strong\u003E - These sutures do not intersect at the bregma\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETemporal and sagittal\u003C/strong\u003E - These sutures do not intersect at the bregma\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESagittal and lamboidal\u003C/strong\u003E - These sutures meet at the lambda, not the bregma\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETemporal and lamboidal\u003C/strong\u003E - These sutures do not intersect at the bregma\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The bregma is a major anatomical landmark on the skull where the coronal and sagittal sutures meet.","The bregma is located at the top of the skull and is used as a reference point in various medical and anthropological measurements."],"references":["Singh, V. (2023). Textbook of Anatomy-Head, Neck and Brain, Volume III-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Patestas, M. A., \u0026 Gartner, L. P. (2016). A textbook of neuroanatomy. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Patel, C. R., Fernandez-Miranda, J. C., Wang, W. H., \u0026 Wang, E. W. (2016). Skull Base Anatomy. Otolaryngologic clinics of North America, 49(1), 9\u201320. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.otc.2015.09.001","Anderson, B. W., Kortz, M. W., Black, A. C., \u0026 Al Kharazi, K. A. (2023). Anatomy, Head and Neck, Skull. In StatPearls. StatPearls Publishing"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58464"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17947"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisio